HEADWORD: Pliers
<hw>Pli"ers</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Ply</er>
to bend, fold.]</ety> <def>A kind of small pinchers with long jaws, --
used for bending or cutting metal rods or wire, for handling small
objects such as the parts of a watch, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pliform</ent>⟦br⟧
